 A List of Networking courses that offer Free certificates

A number of institutes and course providers are offering free Networking courses along with free certificates. Free resources like these are hard to find especially with the tech giants who charge heavily for such courses and certifications.

That's why I think these free resources should be promoted and everyone in the Networking industry including fresh graduates should know about them.

You shouldn't have to pay fees just to learn and practice the core concepts.

Anyways, here is the list of courses I've discovered and thought I should share in this sub-reddit:

    Charles Sturt University - Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) Short course

    Coursera - Cisco Networking Basics Specialization

    Fortinet - Network Security Associate

    Per Scholas - Network Support Certification Track

    OpenEdu - Network Security Course

    SaylorOrg - Computer Communications and Networks

More info on these courses and enrollment details can be found in the Source.

Edit: I removed the Cybrary one because they've started charging money for the CCNA course.
